{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849691247,"sessionID":"ses_2871ce733ffecuUSqQo9hFAVlL","part":{"id":"prt_d78e33ad70018vJwfUCFukmvky","messageID":"msg_d78e324a80018c3PsjTZvzFeTl","sessionID":"ses_2871ce733ffecuUSqQo9hFAVlL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_e19261db84e949d18881fd94","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AR-020: CLI `pack` Command Proposal\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement the `pack` subcommand for the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`), which validates and prepares a workspace, merges CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generates a `Dockerfile`, and reports paths.\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n## Problem Statement\n\nUsers need a CLI command to package an agent workspace into a consistent, validated state ready for subsequent `build`, `publish`, and `invoke` operations. The `pack` command is the entry point to the agent lifecycle — it validates workspace structure, loads or creates metadata, applies CLI overrides, processes language-specific dependencies, and generates a Dockerfile.\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\n### 1. Typer Command Definition (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n\n```python\n@app.command()\ndef pack(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n    language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n    port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n**Success output:** Rich-formatted message with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path` (`{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`).  \n**Error handling:** `_handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)` — prints error in red, traceback if verbose, exits with code 1.\n\n### 2. `PackRuntime` Implementation (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n\nThe `PackRuntime` class orchestrates the packaging workflow:\n\n| Method | Responsibility |\n|--------|----------------|\n| `pack(workspace_path, **options)` | Entry point — runs full pipeline |\n| `_validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)` | Exists, is directory; Python: `*.py` files; Java: `pom.xml` |\n| `_load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options)` | Load `agent_metadata.yaml` (fallback: `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`) or create new |\n| `_apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)` | Merge CLI flags into `AgentMetadata` |\n| `_validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)` | Dispatch to Python/Java validators |\n| `_validate_python_compatibility(workspace_path)` | Check for `*.py` files |\n| `_validate_java_compatibility(workspace_path)` | Check for `pom.xml` |\n| `_process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)` | Dispatch to language-specific dependency processing |\n| `_process_python_dependencies(workspace_path)` | Validate `requirements.txt` existence |\n| `_process_java_dependencies(workspace_path)` | Validate Maven/Gradle setup |\n| `_generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)` | Generate language-appropriate Dockerfile |\n| `_generate_python_dockerfile(metadata)` | Python Dockerfile template |\n| `_generate_java_dockerfile(metadata)` | Java Dockerfile template |\n| `_update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)` | Persist final metadata |\n| `_prepare_output_path(workspace_path, output_path)` | Resolve output directory |\n| `_infer_entrypoint(workspace_path, language)` | Auto-detect entrypoint from workspace files |\n\n### 3. Supporting Components\n\n#### `AgentMetadata` (Pydantic `BaseModel`)\n\n- Fields: `agent_name`, `description`, `language`, `entrypoint`, `port`, `build_mode`, `region`, `version`, `image`, `auth`, `requirements_file`, `registry_*`, `agent_endpoint`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_*`, `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment`\n- Validators: `language` → `['python', 'java']`; `build_mode` → `['local', 'cloud']`; `port` → `1..65535`\n\n#### `MetadataService` (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n\n- `load_metadata(workspace_path)` — Load YAML with fallback chain\n- `save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` — Write `agent_metadata.yaml` with `yaml.dump(exclude_none=True)`\n- `update_metadata(workspace_path, updates)` — Load, merge, save\n- `validate_workspace(workspace_path)` — Language-specific validation\n\n#### `MetadataOptions` (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n\n- Dataclass for CLI option aggregation with `from_options(cls, options)` classmethod\n\n### 4. Workflow\n\n```\npack()\n  ├── Resolve workspace_path\n  ├── PackRuntime(verbose)\n  │   ├── _validate_workspace_structure()\n  │   ├── _load_or_create_metadata()\n  │   ├── _apply_option_overrides()\n  │   ├── _validate_language_compatibility()\n  │   ├── _process_dependencies()\n  │   ├── _generate_dockerfile() (if not exists)\n  │   ├── _update_pack_metadata()\n  │   └── _prepare_output_path()\n  └── Print success with paths\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `typer[all]>=0.9.0` — CLI framework\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0` — Metadata validation\n- `pyyaml>=6.0` — YAML serialization\n- `rich>=13.0.0` — Progress spinner, formatted output\n- `packaging>=23.0` — Version parsing (for future use)\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n1. **Unit tests** for each `PackRuntime` private method with mocked filesystem\n2. **Integration tests** with real workspace directories (Python and Java examples)\n3. **CLI tests** using `typer.testing.CliRunner` for command invocation\n4. **Edge cases:** missing workspace, invalid language, no Python files, missing `pom.xml`, invalid port, Dockerfile already exists\n\n## Risks & Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Workspace validation too strict | Start with minimal checks, iterate based on user feedback |\n| Dockerfile generation conflicts with existing files | Skip generation if Dockerfile exists; add `--force` flag later if needed |\n| Metadata schema evolution | Use Pydantic `Optional` fields with sensible defaults; backward-compatible YAML loading |\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `pack` command accepts all specified options with correct defaults\n- [ ] Workspace validation catches missing directories, wrong language files\n- [ ] Metadata loading falls back through `agent_metadata.yaml` → `agent.yaml` → `metadata.yaml`\n- [ ] CLI overrides merge correctly into existing metadata\n- [ ] Dockerfile generated for both Python and Java agents\n- [ ] Success message displays `agent_name`, `workspace_path`, `metadata_path`\n- [ ] Error handling prints red message + traceback (verbose), exits with code 1\n- [ ] Rich `Progress` spinner shown during work\n- [ ] `--verbose` enables detailed logging via `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775849691232,"end":1775849691242}}}}
